==English==
===Etymology===
From {{i|baseball}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|pos=[[two]] [[for]] [[two]]|-}}

# {{idiom|baseball}} In [[baseball]], meeting two out of two attempts [[at-bat]]. Specifically, it means the batter has reached [[base]] safely two out of two times.
#: He's '''two for two''' tonight.
# Successful at both of two efforts.

====Usage notes====
Also used as adverb, but with few verbs.
: He went '''two for two''' in his last two sales pitches.

